  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18ï½ž70 years of age (Male and Female).

          -  Clinical diagnosis of advanced hepatocellular carcinoma who could accept liver
             transplantation

          -  Patients who had unresectable HCC &gt;5 cm and no metastasis in lungs and bones were
             eligible to participate in this study. Tumor involvement in the intrahepatic and
             extrahepatic portal branches was not considered to be an exclusion criterion.

          -  No prior chemotherapy, radiation therapy, targeted therapy or other kind of biological
             treatment within 4 weeks.

          -  Provide written informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Metastasis in lungs and bones

          -  Invasion in main vescular.

          -  Contraindications of liver transplantation

          -  Contraindications of operation of other organ system

          -  Hypersensitivity to adenovirus, GCV or similar drugs

          -  Accept clinical trials of other drugs

          -  Immunological deficit

          -  Active pregnancy

          -  Unable or unwilling to sign informed consents
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
